features: OUR PROMISE TO YOU: Focusing on what's best for your baby and for the earth, we offer disposable baby diaper alternatives that's free from harmful chemicals, parabens, alcohol, dyes, latex and other preservatives. Our hypoallergenic disposable diapers are composed of pure ingredients sourced from responsibly-managed forests.

RASH FREE BABY DIAPERS: Parasol diaper features RashShield protection which is perfect for your baby's sensitive skin. To prevent diaper rash, the inner lining instantly wicks moisture and locks it down within its super absorbent layers. The all natural diaper has an ultra thin core and a super breathable design that provides absolute comfort.

PERFECT FOR ALL BABIES: Our disposable diapers are great for instant use and clean disposal. Made from stretchable material to enable a wider coverage, these diapers are excellent for toddlers of all sizes. Our disposable diaper packs are also suitable for different age groups making it a great choice for day care centers.

SLEEP WELL, SLEEP TIGHT: Our natural nightime diapers are crafted with breathable fabric to provide absolute comfort for your little one. This super absorbent activewear has an 8-strand retractive waistband and leg cuffs that prevent overflow and side leaks. The extra gentle feel helps your baby sleep through the night feeling dry and breezy.

NATURAL DIAPERS ON THE GO: The natural baby diaper features a sticker tab to effortlessly wrap and conveniently dispose of the used diaper. It rests comfortably against your baby's skin without leaving any marks. Keep your hands mess-free with an easy to remove disposable diaper that's perfect for busy parents who are constantly on the go.
body.description: We listened to your feedback and your dream diaper wishlist, and in response we've created a diaper that's softer, drier, comfier, blowout-proof and that helps prevent diaper rash so baby will stay clear, dry and happy. Rashshield protection instantly wicks moisture away from baby with a soft-as-silk, top-sheet. A dual core of soft, ultra-high absorbency materials is infused with micro-beads which turn to gel on contact with liquid, for a leakproof diaper that dries in seconds. Moisture is evenly distributed and locked down in a thin, even layer without bunching or sagging like traditional diapers. Flexible, interactive leg cuffs and a contour waistband move with your baby without leaks and messy blowouts. We've all been there—baby is finally asleep, but needs a diaper change and noisy pull tabs wake them up. PARASOL whisper-quiet pull tabs let baby sleep peacefully throughout the changing process, (meaning you can catch some extra z’s yourself). PARASOL clear+dry diapers are rigorously tested and certified safe for your baby and planet earth. These distinguished certifications include: Dermatest SEAL OF excellence (no irritation; excellent skin compatibility), RoHS compliant (free Of heavy metals), IECQ (free Of harmful materials; ensures workplace safety), CE (high level of safety, health and environmental requirements), ISO 9001 NQA (world-class standard for quality management system), ISO 14001 CQC (reducing environmental impact and promoting environmental awareness), FSC (Forest Stewardship Council certifies materials are from responsibly managed forests), and SVHC (chemical free). Make sure to keep extra PARASOL clear+dry diapers in your diaper bag or backpack along with PARASOL clear+pure baby wipes—the perfect combo to keep baby clear of irritation, free and happy to explore their world.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the money
reviews.reviewText: I’ve been using huggies and Millie moon diapers for one year, I found these diapers and they are way better! So soft and keep my baby dry even when the diaper is very wet. Will continue to use these. Plus there are no chemicals, dyes, or fragrances!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super soft and absorbant!
reviews.reviewText: We have used honest for our first 2 until we got a sample of these in a box. I decided to just bite the bullet and try a whole bag to see how they were and I love them! They hold more than the same size in honest diapers and I feel like they are wider and just fit my daughter better. I’m sold!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My son sleeps so comfortably and longer than the regular 2 hours with these diapers. He sleeps up to 6 hours with these vs the Huggies. He’ll wake up every 2-3 hours with those. These are life savers at night! We use them at night to ensure we get good sleep.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Super soft but
reviews.reviewText: I recently bought these diapers for my son who has very sensitive skin they are so soft, unfortunately he still gets rashes but not as bad as when he was using other diaper brands. Will not be purchasing again due to the constant over night leakage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars New design is a huge improvement
reviews.reviewText: I stopped using Parasol around 2019 when they changed the design to tacky, terrible prints. I just ordered a few weeks ago and can confirm the diapers you get from amazon are the new adorable design with big improvements including the pee indicator line and better waist elastic.I had been using Parasol since 2017 with my first and was really disappointed when they changed. Recently got an ad and saw they had reverted to super cute patterns and thought I'd give them a chance again. The new design is super soft, they hold well even overnight and have good fit for my second. During the interim I tried pampers and hello bello and I can tell the fit is greatly improved with parasol. The elastic area aroudn the waist actually stretches and the diapers don't sag like hello bello ones.Love the black and white new prints with the leaves and puppies. I like that they're unisex and minimal but I do wish there were more patterns to pick from.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Awful diapers, they leak all the time. They fall apart around the sides and the adhesive part doesn’t work sometimes. I tried out at least 5 or 6 diapers and it happens to all of them. Pretty disappointing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Everything they claim to be
reviews.reviewText: They are super soft! Its designs protect against blowouts and it’s pretty absorbent. Never leave any diaper rash either. I will say the fit is a little wide so it can be awkward trying to put on the diaper but other than that I have no complaints

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Super soft, but will not be buying again.
reviews.reviewText: I was so excited to try these, but I quickly became disappointed in them. I do love that they are a green diaper brand and how soft they are. My baby weighs 16 lbs 8 oz, so he’s right at the beginning bracket for Size 3. We had so many overnight leaks and a couple of blowouts in the leg area. I feel like the waist is too small and the legs are too big. I wanted to love these completely, but they’re a bit disappointing. Guess I’m going back to Coterie.
